    <page type="tailorSection">
        <section>Damage Resistance</section>
        <text>Different types of armor are more effective at stopping attacks than others. This is measured by the damage resistance of the armor,</text>
    </page>

    <page type="tailorSection">
        <section>Damage Threshold</section>
        <text>A tinkers natural inclination is to go for the strongest armors as soon as possible, but even weak armor has its important uses. If the damage of an attack is below the armors 'damage threshold', then it will be absorbed at a resistance rate of 80%. This means even weak armor will be incredibly strong against weak attacks.\n\nIf an armors natural resistance is already above 80%, then the damage threshold will not be calculated.</text>
    </page>

    <page type="tailorSection">
        <section>Modifiers</section>
        <text>Like a tinkers tools, an armor piece can be upgraded to give better stats and abilities.</text>
    </page>

    <page type="tailorSection">
        <section>Protection Modifiers</section>
        <text>Protection modifiers will grant additional protection against certain types of damage. This reduction is applied separately from the armors resistance and damage threshold. It is important to realize however that, all the protection modifiers of an armor set cannot reduce an attack by more than 80%.</text>
    </page>


    <page type="tailorModifier">
        <modifier>normal</modifier>
        <desc>Protection against 'normal' damage. This will protect against fire, explosion, projectiles and any physical based attacks. It won't protect against non-physical damage such as magical, poison or wither attacks.</desc>
    </page>

    <page type="tailorModifier">
        <modifier>fire</modifier>
        <desc>Protects against fire damage.</desc>
    </page>


    <page type="tailorModifier">
        <modifier>explosion</modifier>
        <desc>Protects against shock waves caused by explosions.</desc>
    </page>


    <page type="tailorModifier">
        <modifier>projectile</modifier>
        <desc>Protection against damage caused by ranged projectiles..</desc>
    </page>


    <page type="tailorModifier">
        <modifier>magic</modifier>
        <desc>Protection against magical or non-physical attacks. Such as poison, potions of harming, wither attacks, etc.</desc>
    </page>

    <page type="tailorModifier">
        <modifier>wither</modifier>
        <desc>Protection against the withering effect. This will not protect against the direct wither attack.</desc>
    </page>

    <page type="tailorModifier">
        <modifier>fall</modifier>
        <desc>Protection against falling.</desc>
    </page>

    <page type="tailorModifier">
